From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kandelo <noreply@kandelo.invalid>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Keep trusted publisher taps usable with immutable trust

Kandelo's bottle publisher gives Formula evaluation a root-owned, read-only
trust store. Homebrew still attempts to persist a redundant per-item entry for
every fully qualified install, even when the containing tap is already trusted.
That write fails before a Formula can run.

Skip the automatic per-item persistence when the tap already grants the same
authority. Explicit `brew trust` operations still use the normal mutation path
and fail against an immutable publisher store. This patch is applied only to
the publisher's temporary Homebrew overlay; guest Homebrew keeps its normal
trust behavior.
---
 Library/Homebrew/trust.rb | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb b/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb
+++ b/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb
@@ -121,3 +121,4 @@ module Homebrew
         item_name = ::Utils.name_from_full_name(name)
         tap = Tap.fetch(tap_name)
+        next if trusted_tap?(tap)
         next if tap.official?
